article.headline: Chattanooga 70, Ball St. 55
article.story: MUNCIE, Ind. (AP) -- Nicchaeus Doaks scored 19 points on 8-of-9 shooting and grabbed eight rebounds to lead Chattanooga to a 70-55 victory over Ball State Tuesday night. Casey Long added 16 points and Keddric Mays had 14 for the Mocs (2-2), who trailed 33-26 at halftime. Chattanooga built a 54-50 lead with 6:31 left to play and then went on a 16-5 run to take control of the game, outscoring the Cardinals 44-22 in the second half. Micah Rollin led the Cardinals (2-1) with 16 points, including 10-of-13 from the free throw line and eight rebounds. Jalon Perryman scored 15 points for Ball State and Anthony Newell had 13 points and 10 rebounds. The Cardinals outrebounded Chattanooga 38-36 and as a result had a 18-11 advantage in second-chance points. Ball State shot just 2-of-29 (7 percent) from 3-point range.
